Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}.

Trim the @Iceberg Lettuce{1} and thinly slice.

Slit the sausage skins lengthways, remove the skin and discard. Put the @British Honey Mustard Sausages{4} meat in a #bowl{} and use your hands to combine it together. Roll the sausage meat into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

Pop the burgers onto a baking tray.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

When the wedges have 15 mins remaining, bake the burgers on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{14-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While everything cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay in the @British Streaky Bacon{4%rashers} and fry until crispy and brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side.

Transfer to a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{} and set aside for later.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Once the burgers are cooked, carefully place the cheese on top of the burgers. Pop the @Sliced Burger Buns{2} onto the same tray, cut side up.

Return the tray to the oven until the cheese has melted and the buns have warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine the dressed lettuce with the @Burger Sauce{45%grams}. Toss together until well coated.

When everything's ready, spread the @Mayonnaise{1%tbsp} over the bun bases and @BBQ Sauce{32%grams} over the lids.

Top the bases with the cheeseburger, some dressed lettuce and crispy bacon, then sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve your burgers with the wedges and remaining dressed lettuce alongside.

Enjoy!